      <span class="eyebrow">The idea</span>
      <h2>Why "Operations Partner" Is the Honest Title</h2>
      <p>Abraham Otieno is a Nairobi-based fractional operations partner for founders and CEOs in the US, Europe, and Africa. The title comes from a client, Salome, Lead of Partnerships at Dial Africa: <em>"He's more than an assistant; he's a true operations partner."</em> It's the most accurate description of how these engagements actually run.</p>
      <p>Here's the founder's real problem: at 5–80 people you need executive support <em>and</em> an operating rhythm <em>and</em> reliable systems, but each of those is a part-time need. Hiring three people creates coordination overhead worse than the problem. Hiring one junior generalist creates work for you. The model that fits: one senior operator, fractional hours, covering the full surface.</p>

      <h2 style="margin-top: var(--space-7);">The Three Surfaces I Cover</h2>
      <ul style="color: var(--ink-muted); padding-left: var(--space-5);">
        <li><strong>Executive support</strong>: calendar architecture, inbox triage, meeting prep, board pack assembly, travel. The 15+ hours a week you're currently losing. (Full scope: <a href="/executive-assistant-to-ceo/">EA to CEO</a>.)</li>
        <li><strong>Operating cadence</strong>: leadership rhythm, decision logs, OKR check-ins, investor update discipline. (Full scope: <a href="/virtual-chief-of-staff/">virtual chief of staff</a>.)</li>
        <li><strong>Operations systems</strong>: SLA tracking, CRM dashboards, onboarding playbooks, SOPs. The work behind 80% faster team response and 200+ agents onboarded. (Full scope: <a href="/operations-manager-kenya/">remote operations manager</a>.)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>In any given week the mix shifts: that's the point. The bottleneck moves; the engagement follows it.</p>

      <h2 style="margin-top: var(--space-7);">What This Looks Like in Practice</h2>
      <p>A typical week: Monday, run your leadership meeting prep and circulate last week's decision log. Tuesday–Wednesday, own your inbox triage and push the partnership launch you don't have time to chase. Thursday, tighten the support team's SLA dashboard and flag the two metrics drifting. Friday, your weekly status report: what moved, what's blocked, what needs your decision. You read one document instead of chasing ten threads.</p>
      <p>Past engagements in this shape: stakeholder-CEO coordination at Generation Kenya ("transformed our team dynamics" — Mathew, Lead of Operations), service transition management at Insight BPO, and partnership coordination at Dial Africa. <a href="/case-studies/">Case studies here</a>.</p>

      <h2 style="margin-top: var(--space-7);">Start with the Bottleneck</h2>
      <p><a href="/booking/">Book a free 30-minute consultation</a>. We'll map where your week leaks, which surface needs me first, and what the first 30 days deliver. If a narrower engagement fits better (pure EA, pure CoS, pure ops), I'll tell you that instead. No pitch.</p>
